==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sheal
<hw>Sheal</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To put under a sheal or
shelter.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sheal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sheal
<hw>Sheal</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Shell</er>.]</ety>
<def>To take the husks or pods off from; to shell; to empty of its
contents, as a husk or a pod.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng. &
Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That's a <qex>shealed</qex> peascod.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sheal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Sheal
<hw>Sheal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A shell or pod.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

